  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "The Freudian concept, radicalized by Lacan, of a force that operates beyond the pleasure principle — unbinding, disintegrating, and returning to zero. For anarcho-nihilism, the death drive names the structural position of what the symbolic order cannot integrate: the force that disrupts every system's self-reproduction.",
  "keywords": "anarchism, psychoanalysis",
  "name": "The Death Drive",
